<BaseLayout title="Affiliate disclosure" description="How Stay Safe Guide makes money, and our promise on recommendations.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>Affiliate disclosure</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: 4 June 2026</em></p>

    <p>Stay Safe Guide is free to read. To keep it that way, some of the links on this
    site are affiliate links. If you click one and go on to buy or sign up, we may earn
    a small commission. This comes out of the company's marketing budget, so it never
    costs you anything extra.</p>

    <h2>Our promise</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Commission never decides what we recommend. We pick what we believe is genuinely best for the reader, then look for an affiliate link, not the other way round.</li>
      <li>We tell you when a free option does the job, even when a paid one would earn us more.</li>
      <li>We only recommend products and services we would be comfortable setting up for our own family.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Where we take part in affiliate programmes (for example the Amazon Associates
    programme and the programmes run by VPN, password manager, antivirus and
    identity-protection providers), we will say so clearly on the relevant pages.
    As an Amazon Associate, we earn from qualifying purchases.</p>

    <p>This disclosure is made in line with UK Advertising Standards Authority guidance
    and the Competition and Markets Authority's rules on clearly labelling paid links.</p>

    <p>Questions about this? <a href="/contact/">Contact us</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
